# UI file rules

When creating or editing UI files in this repo:

1. Import `nst-design-system.css` (not standalone token files unless extending the system).
2. Map each UI element to `COMPONENTS.md` before coding.
3. Copy structure from the matching `preview/*.html` specimen when one exists.
4. Allowed inline styles: layout only (`max-width`, `minmax()`, `grid-template-columns`). Not colors, fonts, padding, or borders.
5. New dashboard/card UI → `.vw-card-*` + `.vw-chip-*` only.
6. New forms/tables → `.nst-*` from `components.css` after reading `preview/inputs-states.html` or `preview/table.html`.

If no registry match exists, say so and propose adding to the design system — do not invent a one-off design.
